{# Template: docproc/extract-hmems.j2 #}
{# Goal: Extract RDF triples from text with confidence scores. #}
{# Type: KnowAct — rendered by hkask-mcp-docproc via minijinja #}

Extract up to {{ limit | default(10) }} factual RDF triples from the following text.

Each triple should be in the form (subject, predicate, object) where:
- subject: an entity mentioned in the text (prefix with '{{ namespace | default("corpus") }}:')
- predicate: a relationship or property (use standard RDF predicates: rdf:type, schema:name, schema:author, schema:mentions, schema:relatedTo)
- object: another entity, a literal value, or a type

For each triple, also provide a confidence score (0.0-1.0) based on how clearly the text supports it.

Example: {"subject": "corpus:Damodaran", "predicate": "schema:author", "object": "Investment Valuation", "confidence": 0.98}

Text:
{{ text }}

Respond in JSON format:
{"h_mems": [{"subject": "...", "predicate": "...", "object": "...", "confidence": 0.95}]}
